ible interest, never as a fact about the user's nationality, home location, vacation schedule, budget, travel style, or preferences.\\n\\nCampaign key: nearby_trip_planning\\nCreative theme: planning a refreshing nearby getaway within roughly two to three hours from home.\\nDemonstrated request: \\\"夏休みにリフレッシュがてら家から2~3時間で行ける旅行を考えてるんだけど、チャッピーどう思う？\\\"\\nUseful workflow for later turns: learn the starting area, travel radius, transportation, timing, interests, and constraints; compare nearby destinations; choose one; then refine an itinerary.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Offer a simple way to begin planning a two-to-three-hour getaway.\\n- Do not ask for the starting area, transportation, timing, or preferences in prose; let the continuation choices gather those details.\\n- Do not assume the user's location or invent nearby destinations before learning it.\\n- If the user changes topics later, help normally.\"},\"hairstyle_analysis\":{\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid Meta or Instagram campaign. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, appearance, gender, hair, photos, language preference, or plans to change their hairstyle.\\n\\nCampaign key: hairstyle_analysis\\nCreative theme: using a portrait to compare several hairstyle directions in a clean, high-resolution visual guide.\\nDemonstrated request: create a portrait-and-panel hairstyle graphic with four or five options and practical tips.\\nUseful workflow for later turns: gather a clear portrait and desired level of change, preserve identity, propose suitable style directions without presenting appearance judgments as facts, visualize the options, and explain tradeoffs.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Make hairstyle exploration feel fun and low-commitment, with concrete value around comparing options, visualizing a change, and getting practical styling guidance.\\n- Do not assume the user has uploaded a photo, wants a haircut, or has any particular face shape, hair texture, or style.\\n- Let the continuation choices offer a hairstyle comparison, a subtle refresh, and a bolder visual preview.\\n- If the user changes language or topics later, follow their lead and help normally.\",\"enabled\":true},\"cricket_catchup\":{\"enabled\":true,\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid YouTube campaign. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, country, language, location, or durable interests.\\n\\nCampaign key: cricket_catchup\\nCreative theme: quickly catching up after missing the first hour of a cricket match.\\nDemonstrated request: \\\"I missed the first hour of the cricket, summarise what's happened so far.\\\"\\nUseful workflow for later turns: identify the match and missed window, then provide a concise, current recap covering match state, momentum shifts, key events, and what matters next.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Offer a fast cricket catch-up without pretending a match has already been identified.\\n- Do not ask for the match or missed window in prose; let the continuation choices gather those details.\\n- Do not invent a score, teams, tournament, or events. For live or recent matches, browse once the user identifies the event.\\n- If the user changes topics later, help normally.\"},\"background_cleanup\":{\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid TikTok campaign presented in Spanish. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, appearance, photos, location, language preference, or editing needs.\\n\\nCampaign key: background_cleanup\\nCreative theme: cleaning up a personal photo by removing distracting people or objects from the background while preserving the main subject and the rest of the scene.\\nDemonstrated request: remove everyone in the background and leave every other part of the photo unchanged.\\nUseful workflow for later turns: gather the photo, identify exactly what should disappear, preserve the subject and composition, generate a natural-looking edit, and refine any awkward filled areas.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Make precise cleanup feel quick and satisfying, with concrete value around preserving what matters, removing distractions, and keeping the edit natural.\\n- Do not assume the user has uploaded a photo, is the person pictured, or wants any specific element removed.\\n- Let the continuation choices offer a clean background, removal of one distraction, and a polished alternate crop.\\n- If the user changes language or topics later, follow their lead and help normally.\",\"enabled\":true},\"photo_comic_story\":{\"enabled\":true,\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid Meta campaign presented in Indonesian. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, relationships, photos, fandoms, language preference, or preferred story.\\n\\nCampaign key: photo_comic_story\\nCreative theme: turning reference photos and a shared memory or playful premise into a personalized black-and-white manga or comic.\\nDemonstrated scenario: friends become characters in a humorous romantic manga built from their photos and a real creative backstory.\\nUseful workflow for later turns: gather reference photos and a short premise, preserve recognizable details, choose tone and panel style, draft a compact story beat, then generate a cohesive comic sequence.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Make personal storytelling feel warm and imaginative, with concrete value around casting real references, shaping a fun premise, and creating a shareable comic.\\n- Do not assume the user has uploaded photos, wants romance or manga, knows the featured people, or shares the creator's relationships.\\n- Let the continuation choices offer a photo-based comic, a memory turned into panels, and a different visual genre.\\n- If the user changes language or topics later, follow their lead and help normally.\"},\"personal_color_analysis\":{\"enabled\":true,\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid Meta campaign presented in Hindi. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, appearance, skin tone, gender, photos, location, language preference, or beauty preferences.\\n\\nCampaign key: personal_color_analysis\\nCreative theme: using a portrait to create visual color, makeup, and hairstyle analysis boards with side-by-side comparisons and concise labels.\\nDemonstrated request: create a visual-first makeup analysis graphic from a portrait, compare suitable options, and show the subject's undertone without long paragraphs.\\nUseful workflow for later turns: gather a clear portrait, choose whether to focus on colors, makeup, hair, or outfits, create a visual comparison, explain uncertainty, and refine based on the user's taste.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Make visual style exploration feel accessible and confidence-building, with concrete value around color palettes, side-by-side comparisons, and personalized mockups.\\n- Do not infer the user's undertone, features, gender, style, or that a photo has already been uploaded.\\n- Let the continuation choices offer a color palette, a makeup comparison, and a hairstyle or outfit visualization.\\n- If the user changes topics later, help normally while retaining this context only as a soft preference signal.\"},\"photo_annotation\":{\"enabled\":true,\"bootstrap_context\":\"You are starting a conversation with a user who arrived from a paid Meta or Instagram campaign. Treat this as a soft signal of possible interest, never as a fact about the user's identity, photos, belongings, location, or creative preferences.\\n\\nCampaign key: photo_annotation\\nCreative theme: adding tasteful handwritten annotations, arrows, outlines, and small doodles to make an everyday photo feel expressive and story-ready.\\nDemonstrated request: identify meaningful elements in a photo, add concise subject-aware notes, and preserve generous negative space.\\nUseful workflow for later turns: gather the photo and desired mood, identify a few strong annotation opportunities, create a restrained visual treatment, and refine density or tone.\\n\\nFor the first visible response:\\n- Make the transformation feel personal and shareable, with concrete value around visual storytelling, a cohesive annotation style, and a polished composition.\\n- Do not assume the user has uploaded a photo, wants every object labeled, or prefers the featured white-line style.\\n- Let the continuation choices offer a handwritten story layer, a minimal doodle treatment, and a different annotation mood.\\n- If the user changes topics later, help normally.\"}}},\"is_device_based\":true,\"passed\":false},\"1299917208\":{\"name\":\"1299917208\",\"rule_id\":\"default\",\"secondary_exposures\":[],\"id_type\":\"stableID\",\"value\":{\"handoff_link_strategy\":\"legacy_root\"},\"is_device_based\":true,\"passed\":false},\"2302071098\":{\"name\":\"2302071098\",\"rule_id\":\"default\",\"secondary_exposures\":[],\"id_type\":\"userID\",\"value\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https://persistent.oaistatic.com/deep-research/nux.070152025.mp4\",\"posterUrl\":\"https://persistent.oaistatic.com/deep-research/nux.070152025.jpg\"},\"is_device_based\":false,\"passed\":false},\"1249441125\":{\"name\":\"1249441125\",\"rule_id\":\"default\",\"secondary_exposures\":[],\"id_type\":\"userID\",\"value\":{},\"is_device_based\":false,\"passed\":false},\"3774971069\":{\"name\":\"3774971069\",\"rule_id\":\"3wuW1nDxShKMpRhW6RD9w6-3wuW1lYvpZBi6rK0vJHwd4\",\"secondary_exposures\":[],\"id_type\":\"userID\",\"value\":{\"tooltip\":\"Only includes tokens tracked after token-based pricing wa